    <summary>Complete TON file format implementation with parser, validator, and serializer for .NET</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
## Version 1.0.0 - Initial Release

Developed by DevPossible, LLC
Contact: support@devpossible.com

### Features
- Full TON specification support
- Robust recursive descent parser with comprehensive error reporting
- Built-in schema validation with custom rules and constraints
- Flexible serialization with multiple output formats
- Strong typing with automatic type inference and conversion
- Native array syntax support with validation
- Enum and EnumSet support
- Type annotations and type hints
- Object hierarchy with class names and instance counts
- Support for comments (single-line and multi-line)
- Multiple number formats (decimal, hex, binary, scientific notation)
- GUID support
- Async file operations
- Performance optimized

### Supported Data Types
- Primitives: string, integer, float, boolean, null, undefined
- Special types: GUID, Date (ISO 8601)
- Number formats: Hexadecimal (0xFF), Binary (0b1010), Scientific notation
- Collections: Arrays with mixed types and nesting
- Enums: Single values and sets
- Objects: Nested structures with optional class typing

### API Highlights
- TonParser for parsing from files, strings, and streams
- TonSerializer with customizable serialization options
- TonValidator for schema-based validation
- TonDocument, TonObject, and TonValue for data manipulation
- Conversion between TON and C# objects
- Property path navigation
- Comprehensive error handling

For detailed usage and examples, visit the project repository.

For support, contact: support@devpossible.com
